'''Rape van''' is a colloquial term used to describe a van or similar vehicle with characteristics that make it well suited for use in enabling the user to carry out the [[rape]] of victims. These include:
#an absence of [[window]]s along the body of the van, or windows that are heavily [[Window tinting|tinted]], [[curtain]]ed or painted over so that those outside the vehicle can not easily see in
#side or rear doors that open and close quickly and easily, so that individuals inside the van can jump out, seize a passerby, force them into the vehicle, and close the doors behind them
#an open interior space without rear passenger seats, which facilitates both forcing a victim into the van and then assaulting the victim while in the van.

Use of such vehicles has been reported in the news, and has been depicted on [[police procedural]]s such as ''[[Law & Order]]'', ''[[CSI: Crime Scene Investigation|CSI]]'', and ''[[Homicide: Life on the Street]]''.

